% time $t$, $Core{ }Score_{r,c,t}$, is given by its h-index $h_r$ multiplied by the number of publications $r$ has in $c$ during $t$ ($\textrm{\#}publications_{r,c,t}$),
% as expressed by Equation~\ref{eq:core_score}. 
